%208%2C000%20trucks%20and%20lorries%20were%20accepted%20to%20pass%20through%20Russia.%20However%2C%20this%20number%20is%20set%20as%20at%20a%20maximum%20of%202%2C000%20for%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJoint%20Activities%20Suspended%20at%20Government%20Level%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECommercial%20and%20economic%20activities%20between%20Turkey%20and%20Russia%20at%20the%20government%20level%20have%20been%20suspended.%20However%20the%20Russian%20government%20has%20appointed%20their%20Ministry%20of%20Economy%20to%20negotiate%20with%20Turkey%20about%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20The%20bilateral%20Agreement%20on%20Trade%20in%20Services%20and%20Investments%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20The%20Middle-term%20program%20for%20economic%2C%20trade%2C%20scientific%2C%20technical%20and%20cultural%20cooperation%20for%202016-2019%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20Formation%20of%20the%20joint%20Fund%20for%20Financing%20Investment%20Projects%20in%20Russia%20and%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20sanctions%20directly%20affect%20Turkey%2C%20Turkish%20companies%20and%20Turkish%20citizens.%20However%2C%20they%20also%20indirectly%20affect%20many%20European%20and%20American%20companies.%20Some%20of%20these%20companies%20face%20severe%20procurement%20problems%20where%20they%20have%20production%20facilities%20in%20Russia%2C%20yet%20source%20raw%20materials%20or%20parts%20required%20for%20these%20facilities%20from%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it%20is%20positive%20that%20the%20sanctions%20exclude%20on-going%20investment%20undertakings%20in%20Russia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20gas%20exportation%20to%20Turkey.%20These%20are%20the%20two%20largest%20goods%20and%20services%20exchanged%20between%20the%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20penal%20clause%20or%20compensation%20claims%20will%20inevitably%20arise%20for%20Turkish%20and%20foreign%20parties%20which%20are%20unable%20to%20fulfill%20their%20undertakings%20and%20are%20forced%20to%20cancel%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20serious%20and%20legitimate%20concerns%20exist%20regarding%20the%20rights%20and%20obligations%20of%20parties%20involved%20in%20agreements%20which%20are%20already%20executed%20in%20Turkey%20for%20future%20expected%20businesses%20in%20Russia%2C%20or%20agreements%20which%20would%20have%20been%20executed%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20on-going%20agreements%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParties%20who%20are%20obliged%20to%20provide%20goods%20or%20services%20are%20preparing%20to%20file%20for%20objective%20impossibility%20and%20force%20majeure%20objections.%20Meanwhile%2C%20parties%20which%20have%20made%20a%20payment%20or%20submitted%20a%20guarantee%20letter%20are%20preparing%20for%20collection%20of%20penal%20clauses%20and%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestment%20arbitration%20against%20Russia%20is%20considered%20possible%20for%20investors%20whose%20long%20term%20undertakings%20are%20affected%20by%20the%20sanctions.%20Investors%20would%20be%20able%20to%20seek%20penal%20and%20compensation%20amounts%20which%20they%20might%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20breach%20of%20these%20undertakings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20government%20%E2%80%93%20as%20if%20acknowledging%20the%20affects%20and%20results%20of%20the%20sanctions%20which%20cause%20a%20logarithmic%20domino%20effect%20for%20governments%20and%20companies%20%E2%80%93%20has%20given%20some%20signals%20indicating%20that%20the%20sanctions%20will%20be%20eased.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20is%20speculated%20that%20the%20Russian%20Ministry%20of%20Commerce%20is%20working%20on%20draft%20legislation%20to%20ease%20the%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20stadiums%20and%20other%20facilities%20required%20to%20be%20built%20for%20the%20FIFA%20World%20Cup%20to%20be%20held%20in%20Russia%20in%202018%2C%20Sberbank%E2%80%99s%20activities%20in%20Turkey%2C%20Rosatom%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20center%20in%20Turkey%2C%20as%20well%20as%20all%20other%20commercial%20projects%20and%20benefits%2C%20the%20clear%20preference%20is%20to%20lift%20the%20sanctions%20altogether.%20However%2C%20if%20this%20cannot%20be%20done%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20it%20is%20best%20for%20both%20Turkey%20and%20Russia%20to%20ease%20these%20sanctions%20to%20keep%20the%20commercial%20effects%20at%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22ImageUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ImagePosition%22%3A0%7D%5D%2C%22TestCities%22%3A%5B%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%220%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Adana%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%221%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Ad%C4%B1yaman%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%222%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Afyonkarahisar%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%223%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22A%C4%9Fr%C4%B1%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%224%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Aksaray%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%225%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Amasya%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%226%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Ankara%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%227%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Antalya%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%228%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Ardahan%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%229%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Artvin%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2210%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Ayd%C4%B1n%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2211%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bal%C4%B1kesir%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2212%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bart%C4%B1n%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2213%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Batman%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2214%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bayburt%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2215%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bilecik%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2216%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bing%C3%B6l%22%7D%2C%7B%22CountryID%22%3A%22182%22%2C%22ID%22%3A%2217%22%2C%22Name%22%3A%22Bitlis%22%7D%2C%7B%22Countr